      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, a router does not track individual locations or the signal strength of specific devices across your house in real-time. Your neighbor likely simply intends the new name to be a humorous reminder for you to go eat after watching \"A Quiet Place.\" While you might suspect you have a \"security setup\" gone wrong due to the glitchy signal, this is almost certainly just normal radio interference or overlapping networks rather than surveillance.",
